            <note xml:id="foot.f2">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-12998.xml">letter to Ernst Krause, 10 January 1881</ref>. CD had asked <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_258.xml">Francis Maitland Balfour</ref> to translate Krause’s reply to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_774.xml">Samuel Butler</ref> for <hi rend="italic">Nature</hi> (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-13007.xml">letter to F. M. Balfour, 12 January 1881</ref> and n. 2).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">CD had been highly critical of parts of <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4303.xml">Anna Seward</ref>’s biography of <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1219.xml">Erasmus Darwin</ref> (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_7126.xml">A. Seward 1804</ref>; see <hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi> vol. 27, letters <ref target="./DCP-LETT-11932.xml">to Ernst Krause, 14 March 1879</ref> and <ref target="./DCP-LETT-11944.xml">19 March 1879</ref>, and <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2365.xml"><hi rend="italic">Erasmus Darwin</hi></ref>, pp. 70–9).</note>
        
